snippet.title: YUNGBLUD - live at Pinkpop 2024
snippet.description:
0:00 I Love You, Will You Marry Me
4:00 fleabag
11:17 breakdown.
15:04 Lowlife

http://www.3voor12.nl/pinkpop

PINKPOP 2024 BIJ DE NPO 
Ook dit jaar (her)beleef je Pinkpop weer volop op tv, radio en online bij de NPO! Tijdens het weekend maar ook daarna. De Pinkpop 2024 uitzendingen worden verzorgd door NTR, VPRO & BNNVARA. 
Presentatoren Vera Siemons, Frank Evenblij en Eva Cleven doen op NPO3 vanaf het festivalterrein verslag van de vele indrukwekkende optredens, bespreken de meest opvallende momenten en nemen je mee naar de artiesten backstage. 
Via NPO Start kan je de uitzendingen na het festival natuurlijk ook terugkijken! Op NPO 2 Extra worden tijdens het Pinkpop weekend complete optredens gestreamd en die zijn na afloop terug te vinden op het YouTube-kanaal van 3voor12. 
Op de website van 3voor12 vind je ook recensies van de optredens. 3FM zendt live uit vanaf het festivalterrein en via 3fm.nl/festival zijn na afloop alle highlights terug te vinden. Nagenieten doe je ook met: de Pinkpop After podcast op NPO Luister en Pinkpop Napret, van 24 tot 28 juni vanaf 22.15 op NPO 2 Extra.

••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​••​​​•​••​••​••​••​••​​​•​••​••​​​•​​​
VPRO 3voor12 is het belangrijkste muziekplatform van Nederland. Check onze website voor muzieknieuws,  achtergrondverhalen, festivalverslagen en alles daartussen in. Op NPO 3FM is elke vrijdagavond 3voor12 Radio van 22-01. In dit programma draaien we de allerbeste muziek van vandaag én morgen, bespreken we de actualiteit en verwelkomen we artiesten live in de studio.

3voor12 by Dutch Public Broadcasting Company VPRO is the leading music platform in The Netherlands. 3voor12 also has two shows on Dutch national public radio station 3FM.

snippet.title: 【Classic Rock 1970】Free, Chicago, Santana, Led Zeppelin, Emerson, Lake & Palmer
snippet.description: The Beatles disband, releasing their last album, Let It Be, and all four members begin successful solo careers. The Isle of Wight Festival is held in the UK and attracts over 600,000 spectators, surpassing Woodstock. Drugs claimed the lives of rock stars Jimi Hendrix and Janis Joplin. Simon and Garfunkel broke up and their album ``Bridge Over Troubled Water'' reached number one in the world. British band Black Sabbath releases their self-titled debut album, considered by many to be the first "heavy metal" album. The Jackson 5 have four US #1 singles.

snippet.title: 【Classic Rock 1973】Elton John, Grand Funk Railroad, T-Rex, Queen, Bob Marley, Stevie Wonder
snippet.description: Led Zeppelin drew 56,800 people to Tampa Stadium, breaking the Beatles' record for the largest attendance for a concert at Shea Stadium. Summer Jam in Watkins Glen, New York, broke the Woodstock record with 600,000 fans seeing The Band, The Allman Brothers, and the Grateful Dead. On US television, the concert series ``Midnight Special'' and ``Don Kirshner's Rock Concert'' begin, featuring musical acts who perform live rather than lip-syncing. On radio, The King Biscuit Flour Hour debuts with weekly live concert broadcasts. Singer-songwriter Jim Croce dies in a plane crash in Louisiana.

snippet.title: 【Classic Rock 1969】The Rolling Stones,  Bob Dylan, The Beatles, The Who, Led Zeppelin,King Crimson
snippet.description: The Beatles play their final show on the rooftop of Apple Records in London. David Bowie's single "Space Oddity" was a huge hit in the UK and coincided with America's moon landing. The Woodstock Music and Art Fair was held in Bethel, New York, and was attended by 500,000 people. Brian Jones of the Rolling Stones drowns. A man is stabbed to death at a free Rolling Stones concert at Altamont Speedway in California.

snippet.title: Pink Floyd - The Dark Side Of The Moon (50th Anniversary) [2023 Remaster] {Full Album}
snippet.description:
Pink Floyd’s ‘Animals 2018 Remix – Dolby Atmos’ on Blu-ray out now: https://PinkFloyd.lnk.to/AnimalsBluRay

Collector’s Edition of The Dark Side Of The Moon on crystal clear vinyl out now: https://pinkfloyd.lnk.to/TDSOTMUVVinyl a

*TRACKLISTING*
0:00 Speak To Me
1:11 Breathe (In The Air) 
3:57 On The Run
7:30 Time
14:35 The Great Gig In The Sky
19:19 Money
25:48 Us And Them
33:33 Any Colour You Like
36:59 Brain Damage
40:49 Eclipse


*50TH ANNIVERSARY OF PINK FLOYD‘S ‘THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON’. OUT MARCH 24*
Announcing the release of Pink Floyd’s ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ as a deluxe box set to celebrate 50 years since the release of one of the best-selling albums of all time. Newly remastered, the box set will be released on 24th March 2023. 

One of the most iconic and influential albums ever, Pink Floyd’s ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ continues to find new audiences globally. The album was partly developed during live performances, and the band premiered an early version of the suite at London’s Rainbow Theatre several months before recording began. ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ is the eighth studio album by Pink Floyd, originally released in the US on 1 March and then in the UK on 16th March 1973.  The new material was recorded in 1972 and 1973 at EMI Studios (now Abbey Road studios) in London. The iconic sleeve, which depicts a prism spectrum, was designed by Storm Thorgerson of Hipgnosis and drawn by George Hardie. ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ has sold over 50 million copies worldwide.

The new deluxe box set includes CD and gatefold vinyl of the new 2023 remastered studio album and Blu-Ray + DVD audio featuring the original 5.1 mix and remastered stereo versions.  The set also includes additional new Blu-ray disc of Atmos mix plus CD and LP of ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon - Live At Wembley Empire Pool, London, 1974’. For full details see listing below.


THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON STUDIO ALBUM CREDITS:
1 SPEAK TO ME (Nick Mason)
2 BREATHE (IN THE AIR) (Roger Waters, David Gilmour, Richard Wright)
3 ON THE RUN (David Gilmour, Roger Waters)
4 TIME (Nick Mason, Roger Waters, Richard Wright, David Gilmour)
5 THE GREAT GIG IN THE SKY (Richard Wright - Vocal composition on The Great Gig In The Sky by Clare Torry)
6 MONEY (Roger Waters)
7 US AND THEM (Roger Waters, Richard Wright)
8 ANY COLOUR YOU LIKE (David Gilmour, Nick Mason, Richard Wright)
9 BRAIN DAMAGE (Roger Waters)
10 ECLIPSE (Roger Waters)
 
DAVID GILMOUR Vocals, Guitars, VCS3
NICK MASON Percussion, Tape Effects
RICHARD WRIGHT Keyboards, Vocals, VCS3
ROGER WATERS Bass Guitar, Vocals, VCS3, Tape Effects

Produced by PINK FLOYD
Recorded at Abbey Road Studios, London, between May 1972 and January 1973
Engineer Alan Parsons
Assistant Peter James
Mixing supervised by Chris Thomas
Remastered by James Guthrie

Saxophone on ‘Us And Them’ and ‘Money’ Dick Parry
Vocals on ‘The Great Gig In The Sky’ by Clare Torry
Backing Vocals by Doris Troy, Lesley Duncan, Liza Strike, Barry St John

Original Cover Design & Photography by Hipgnosis
Graphics & Artwork by George Hardie N.T.A.
Heartbeat Graphic from an idea by Roger Waters
Prism Photography by Tony May & Storm Thorgerson
Reissue design by Peter Curzon / StormStudios

All Lyrics by ROGER WATERS

Tracks 1,5 and 8 published by Pink Floyd Music Publishers Ltd., administered by Concord Copyrights
Limited for the World excluding USA & Canada. USA & Canada: TRO-Hampshire House Music Publishing Corp.
Tracks 2,3,4 and 7 published by Pink Floyd Music Publishers Ltd., administered by Concord Copyrights
Limited / Roger Waters Music Overseas Ltd., administered by BMG Rights Management (UK) Ltd. for the World excluding USA & Canada. USA & Canada: TRO-Hampshire House Music Publishing Corp.
Tracks 6,9 and 10 published by Roger Waters Music Overseas Ltd., administered by BMG Rights Management (UK) Ltd. for the World excluding USA & Canada. USA & Canada: TRO-Hampshire House Music Publishing Corp.

Original UK release date: March 1973

snippet.title: Pink Floyd - " PULSE " Live 1994 Remastered
snippet.description:
Remastered 2019, 16.9 
Pink Floyd concert video taken from the 20 October 1994 concert at Earls Court, London, England in The Division Bell Tour. It was originally released on VHS and Laserdisc in 1995.
Seconded part of this concert is on my channel, Pink Floyd The Dark Side of the Moon
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ImlFp6QOZRU&t=1968s

There was considerable delay in the release of the DVD edition of Pulse, with new features announced with each setback. The cause of the delays was reputed to be the continued modifications and additions to produce a high-quality release. The previous planned release date of 22 September 2005 for the two-disc DVD set was changed to 10 July 2006 for the UK and Europe, and 11 July 2006 everywhere else.
Tracks
"Shine On You Crazy Diamond" (Concert version) 00:00
"Learning to Fly" 13:24
"High Hopes" 19:00
"Take It Back" 27:16
"Coming Back to Life" 33:16
"Sorrow" 40:05
"Keep Talking" 51:18
"Another Brick in the Wall 58:55
"One of These Days " 01:05:25
Part 2 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ImlFp6QOZRU&t=1258s

snippet.title: The Story Of The Dark Side Of The Moon
snippet.description:
Pink Floyd’s ‘Animals 2018 Remix – Dolby Atmos’ on Blu-ray out now: https://PinkFloyd.lnk.to/AnimalsBluRay

Collector’s Edition of The Dark Side Of The Moon on crystal clear vinyl out now: https://pinkfloyd.lnk.to/TDSOTMUVVinyl 

*50TH ANNIVERSARY OF PINK FLOYD‘S ‘THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON’. OUT MARCH 24*
Announcing the release of Pink Floyd’s ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ as a deluxe box set to celebrate 50 years since the release of one of the best-selling albums of all time. Newly remastered, the box set was released on 24th March 2023. Order here: https://pinkfloyd.lnk.to/DarkSide50th

One of the most iconic and influential albums ever, Pink Floyd’s ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ continues to find new audiences globally. The album was partly developed during live performances, and the band premiered an early version of the suite at London’s Rainbow Theatre several months before recording began. ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ is the eighth studio album by Pink Floyd, originally released in the US on 1 March and then in the UK on 16th March 1973.  The new material was recorded in 1972 and 1973 at EMI Studios (now Abbey Road studios) in London. The iconic sleeve, which depicts a prism spectrum, was designed by Storm Thorgerson of Hipgnosis and drawn by George Hardie. ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’ has sold over 50 million copies worldwide.


*'THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON - LIVE AT WEMBLEY EMPIRE POOL, LONDON, 1974’*
Simultaneously, on 24th March, the CD and first ever vinyl issue of Pink Floyd’s ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon - Live At Wembley Empire Pool, London, 1974’ will be released independently. It was originally recorded in November 1974 as part of the band’s winter tour and this is the first time it will be available as a stand-alone album, with artwork featuring an original 1973 line-drawn cover by George Hardie.

*ANIMATED VIDEO COMPETITION*
The 50th Anniversary release will also be celebrated as Pink Floyd invite a new generation of animators to enter a competition to create music videos for any of the 10 songs on the iconic 1973 album. Pink Floyd has a rich history of collaborating with animators from the beginnings of the band (Ian Emes, Gerald Scarfe etc.), and in some cases the visuals that accompany the songs have become synonymous with the music itself. The 50th Anniversary will be no exception. The band would like to give all animators an opportunity to present a fresh take on these timeless aural works. Animators can enter up to 10 videos, one per song on the album. A winner will be selected from a panel of experts which will include Pink Floyd’s Nick Mason, Aubrey 'Po' Powell (Pink Floyd's creative director) and the BFI (British Film Institute). The deadline for submissions is December 31st 2023. To enter and for more information go to https://www.pinkfloyd.com/competition/

*PINK FLOYD - THE DARK SIDE OF THE MOON: 50TH ANNIVERSARY BOOK*
The book Pink Floyd - The Dark Side Of The Moon: 50th Anniversary will also be published separately by Thames & Hudson on March 24, 2023 to coincide with the box set release. Curated by photographer Jill Furmanovsky and art directed by Hipgnosis co-founder Aubrey Powell, this LP-sized volume showcases rare and previously unseen photographs taken during The Dark Side Of The Moon tours of 1972-1975 and was created with the involvement of the band members.

*NEW PLANETARIUM ALBUM EXPERIENCE ANNOUNCED*
Fifty years on, in recognition of the iconic album and with the help of huge strides in technology, an official full dome experience with stunning visuals of the solar system and beyond and played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon, will be released in Planetariums around the world in March. Contact your local Planetarium for any screening details.

The show itself will be divided between the 10 tracks off the album, in chronological order, each having a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. It promises to be immersive; an all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.

snippet.title: Jimmy Page: How Stairway to Heaven was written - BBC News
snippet.description:
Subscribe to BBC News www.youtube.com/bbcnews
Stairway to Heaven was one of the biggest rock songs of the 1970s - loved, imitated and sometimes parodied. Now Led Zeppelin's classic track is back on the turntable, on a re-mastered version of the band's fourth album. 43 years after its release, the song continues to hold a place in many music fans' hearts.
Guitarist Jimmy Page gives a personal account of how a rock anthem came together.
Camera: Dave O'Neill, Richard Kenny. Editing: Dave O'Neill. Producer: Amanda Bruckshaw

snippet.title: WE WENT FROM PSYCHOSOCIAL TO THIS?! First Time Hearing Corey Taylor - Snuff (Acoustic) Reaction!
snippet.description:
🎤 About Corey Taylor:
Corey Taylor, known primarily as the lead vocalist for the heavy metal bands Slipknot and Stone Sour, showcases a different side of his musical talent with the acoustic version of "Snuff." Originally performed by Slipknot and known for its haunting lyrics and emotional depth, this acoustic rendition strips down the song to its core, highlighting Taylor's powerful vocal delivery and raw emotional expression.

Join us as we listen to Corey Taylor's acoustic performance of "Snuff" for the first time! This version is a departure from the aggressive sound of Slipknot, offering a more intimate and poignant musical experience. Watch our reaction to see how we're moved by the simplicity and emotional weight of this performance.

🎵 What to Expect in This Video:
First Impressions: Our immediate reactions to the gentle guitar intro and the first verse's stark contrast to Slipknot's usual intensity.
Vocal Analysis: Discussing Corey Taylor's expressive vocal technique and how it conveys the song's emotional themes.
Lyric Interpretation: A deep dive into the lyrics of "Snuff," exploring themes of heartache, betrayal, and sorrow.
Overall Impact: Reflecting on the impact of hearing such a powerful song performed acoustically and its ability to connect on a different level than the original.

🤜🤛 Who We Are:
We’re a couple who loves exploring music across a spectrum of genres, delving into how artists express different emotions through various styles. Join us as we uncover the deeper meanings behind songs and appreciate the versatility of talented musicians like Corey Taylor.

👍 Like and Subscribe:
If you enjoyed our reaction to "Snuff" by Corey Taylor, please like, subscribe, and click the bell. We’re excited to share more reactions to both acoustic and electric performances, exploring the range and dynamics of artists known for their powerful music.

snippet.title: RAP FAN'S FIRST TIME HEARING 'Slipknot - Psychosocial ' | Slipknot REACTION
snippet.description:
"Psychosocial" is a song by the American heavy metal band Slipknot, released as a single from their fourth studio album, "All Hope Is Gone" (2008). Slipknot is known for their aggressive musical style, energetic live performances, and distinctive image, often characterized by their matching jumpsuits and unique masks worn by each member.

**Description of the Song "Psychosocial":**
"Psychosocial" is one of Slipknot's notable tracks, combining elements of nu-metal and alternative metal. The song explores themes of alienation, frustration, and the impact of societal pressures on individuals. The lyrics touch on psychological and emotional struggles, and the chorus contains the memorable refrain "The limits of the dead!"

The music itself features intense guitar riffs, powerful percussion, and dynamic shifts in tempo, creating a chaotic and energetic atmosphere that is characteristic of Slipknot's sound. The band's ability to blend heavy instrumentation with melodic elements is showcased in "Psychosocial," making it a standout track in their discography.

**About Slipknot:**
Slipknot was formed in 1995 in Des Moines, Iowa. The band gained widespread recognition for their self-titled debut album released in 1999. Known for their theatrical live performances and the use of unconventional instruments such as turntables and samplers, Slipknot has become a prominent figure in the heavy metal genre.

Over the years, Slipknot has achieved commercial success and critical acclaim, winning Grammy Awards and maintaining a dedicated fanbase. The band's lineup typically consists of nine members, each identified by a unique number and corresponding mask, adding an element of mystery to their identity.

Slipknot's music often delves into dark and introspective themes, exploring the complexities of human emotions and societal issues. Despite their intense and sometimes controversial image, Slipknot has earned respect for their musical innovation and the emotional depth found in their lyrics.

Slipknot was formed in 1995 in Des Moines, Iowa. The band gained widespread recognition for their self-titled debut album released in 1999. Known for their theatrical live performances and the use of unconventional instruments such as turntables and samplers, Slipknot has become a prominent figure in the heavy metal genre.

Over the years, Slipknot has achieved commercial success and critical acclaim, winning Grammy Awards and maintaining a dedicated fanbase. The band's lineup typically consists of nine members, each identified by a unique number and corresponding mask, adding an element of mystery to their identity.

Slipknot's music often delves into dark and introspective themes, exploring the complexities of human emotions and societal issues. Despite their intense and sometimes controversial image, Slipknot has earned respect for their musical innovation and the emotional depth found in their lyrics.

snippet.title: RAP FAN'S FIRST TIME HEARING SLIPKNOT - " THE DEVIL IN " | SLIPKNOT REACTION
snippet.description:
"Slipknot: The Devil in I" is a blistering track from the band's fifth studio album, ".5: The Gray Chapter." Released in 2014, this song serves as a ferocious declaration of resilience and empowerment amidst adversity, while also delving into themes of personal transformation and inner conflict.

The track opens with a menacing and atmospheric introduction, featuring eerie synths and distorted vocals, setting a dark and foreboding tone. This unsettling atmosphere quickly gives way to a barrage of pounding drums, churning guitars, and pulsating basslines as the song kicks into high gear.

Corey Taylor's vocals are a highlight of "The Devil in I," alternating between menacing growls and soaring melodic hooks. His lyrics are cryptic yet evocative, painting a picture of internal struggle and defiance in the face of inner demons. Lines like "Undo these chains, my friend / I'll show you the rage I've hidden" capture the intense emotional intensity of the song, as the protagonist grapples with their own darkness.

The chorus of "The Devil in I" is anthemic and unforgettable, with Taylor's vocals soaring over a backdrop of crushing riffs and thunderous percussion. The refrain, "The devil in I / Is ready to thrive / We'll never survive" is delivered with a sense of defiant resolve, as if embracing the darkness within as a source of strength rather than weakness.

Musically, "The Devil in I" showcases Slipknot's trademark blend of aggression and melody, with razor-sharp guitar riffs, frenetic drumming, and atmospheric synths creating a dense and immersive sonic landscape. The production is slick and polished, yet retains a raw and visceral edge that captures the band's visceral live energy.

Overall, "Slipknot: The Devil in I" is a potent and adrenaline-fueled anthem that captures the band at the height of their powers. With its blend of crushing heaviness, infectious melodies, and thought-provoking lyricism, it stands as a standout track in Slipknot's catalog, resonating with fans of heavy music worldwide.

snippet.title: Therapist Reacts to Toxicity by System of a Down
snippet.description:
Therapist uses System of a Down's song Toxicity to talk about how people often get stuck in a life that feels dreary, hopeless, and boring, and they will often rage against that but quickly go back to living an unfulfilling life. We can use anger, the rage to help us get out of this situation if we are intentional about directing our anger and giving it a purpose instead of just shooting it out into the world.

snippet.title: Therapist reacts to System of a Down - Aerials
snippet.description:
Therapist analyzes the lyrics of "Aerials" by System of a Down to discuss the importance of shifting your perspective and releasing control. Most people think the path to a better life involves controlling every possible aspect of their life, but the truth is there is so much we will never be able to control, and the best path to a free life is by shifting your perspective to a larger 20,000 feet view. This song is a call to release control and trust that at 20,000 feet everything will make sense.

——

snippet.title: Moving to France in our 50s was NOT what we expected.
snippet.description:
To get a 1 year supply of Vitamin D + 5 individual travel packs FREE with your first purchase, go to https://athleticgreens.com/beneaththesurface 

Get 15% off using the code BTS15 when you buy my new course Collaborative Trip Planning on BrightTrip: https://www.brighttrip.com/courses/collaborative-trip-planning

All animations by my son Sky: https://www.youtube.com/@Skymography


In this video, I explore aspects of our nomadic life, as we work really hard towards finding our dream home here in France and setting down some roots. Not exactly an easy process, especially at our age and with all the requisite bouncing around... while simultaneously trying to adapt to and assimilate an entire new culture. Sometimes we're not sure we can do this. The pain and discomfort can be a little too much. And yet, something inside us keeps us going... Join me as I take a deep look at moving to this incredible country. Do we have what it takes to do this? Do we love it here enough to stick it out? And ultimately, after all's been said and done: Is France really it? Timestamps:

 00:00 - Intro
 02:43 - Pinpointing the Area
 04:27- The Food...Oh the Food!
06:10 - Sponsor (Athletic Greens)

 10:19 - Next Time

snippet.description:
My family and I have chosen to move to Nantes, France - a city focused on equitable mobility, proximity to daily essentials, and solidarity. Let me tell you why we feel like moving to France is the right choice and what it means to leave a place that we know so well.

#france #urbanism #cities

snippet.title: Differences in our French Countryside life vs the USA
snippet.description:
Small things in daily life that feel very different than the USA and shape our days as a family living in the French Countryside of the Dordogne. 

Download our free Move-to-France Resource list: https://unique-writer-5502.ck.page/85c59d782f

00:00 How Life is Different
00:50 Store Hours in France
02:36 French School Schedule
04:43 Fresh Food
05:45 Advertising & Commercials
07:14 French Countryside Events
09:29 Small Businesses
11:47 Slow Living in France
14:09 Delivery Services

About Us:
We are an American family of 3 who moved to France for an extended stay adventure in 2022.  
We wanted to experience Europe as more than rushed tourists on a 10-day vacation. To dive into the culture, learn a new language, experience daily life, and truly know what it was like to work and live somewhere other than the US.  

In France, we set up a business, enrolled in a middle school, found housing, and even got our cat a European passport!  

While in the US preparing to leave, the information we found about staying in France for longer than a short vacation was directed at college students, young & single digital nomads, or retirees.  Where was the useful information for families like us?

With a year under our belts in France, we created Baguette Bound to pass on what we have learned.  We hope to make it easier and inspire other families who are interested in experiencing a long stay in France with their families.  Stay tuned for more information on French culture, local travel ideas, and the logistics of moving across the world.  

Contact us or follow our journey @ https://baguettebound.com/


#movetofrance #france  #americansinfrance #expatlife #expatinfrance #expatmistakes #baguettebound #frenchcountryside #frenchcountry #frenchlife #frenchlifestyle

snippet.title: The Process and how much it really COSTS
snippet.description:
This has been the most difficult video we have ever created. What to include, what not to include, is it all too much ? Hours and hours of research and video takes, all compiled to give you insight as to the process of buying a Chateau in France. From concept, style and shopping to what to look for and what to not. The details of making an offer, the process of the purchase, and receiving your keys. We use our Chateau as an example and discuss the financial end of the deal, what we paid, how much all of the taxes and fees were, as well as the win or loose situation of exchange rates. 

There is a lot of information in this video, and so much more we could have included. If there is further information you would like to know be sure to leave us a comment and we will answer your question to the best of our ability. 

Be sure to watch for our follow up video all about renovating in France !! Please enjoy!

The links...
Anna Sirinides, property finder and buyers agent - anna.sirinides@gmail.com

thefrenchpropertyfinders - Instagram, https://www.instagram.com/thefrenchpropertyfinders/

dreamfrenchproperties - Instagram, https://www.instagram.com/dreamfrenchproperties/

Demande de Valeur Foncière - https://app.dvf.etalab.gouv.fr/

We are at the beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us on this fascinating journey.

Notaires de Paris - https://paris.notaires.fr/fr/outils-et-services/calcul-de-frais-d-achat

About us
Two American boys from California following a dream to purchase and restore a Historic Monument in the south of France. 

Our Channel, At the Chateau, focuses on the restoration and celebration of Château Avensac, a listed French castle, designed in the late 18th century, and built in the beginning of the 19th century, on the ruins of the original 14th century Château.

In 2015 we began an adventure to own a French Chateau. It has been a long journey, and in September of 2021 we became the guardians of this incredible property that we now call home. I keep an ongoing record of the long road to Château ownership, as well as our continued restoration work on our website. You can visit our website by clicking on the following link... https://www.atthechateau.com -
If you would like to receive my newsletter that announces new posts, please visit the website and subscribe.

You can also find us on instagram at atthechateau.france or https://www.instagram.com/atthechateau.france/

And FaceBook at https://www.facebook.com/atthechateau.france

We would like to thank all of our Patrons who are helping to restore this historic monument, their contributions are invaluable to our efforts. If you would like to become a patron of Château Avensac, follow this link, https://www.patreon.com/chateauavensac

snippet.description:
Welcome to Château Avensac. Today we explore the mysterious building adjacent to the Chateau. Join Phillip as we discover the secrets of the Chai du Vin - the Wine Chai.

We are at the very beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us for this fascinating journey.

Des sous-titres français sont disponibles pour cette vidéo en cliquant sur le bouton sous-titres et en choisissant la langue française... profitez-en !

About us
Two American boys following a dream to purchase and restore a Historic Monument in the south of France. Welcome to Château Avensac!

Our Channel, At the Chateau, will focus on the restoration and celebration of this listed French castle designed in the late 18th century, and built in the beginning of the 19th century, on the ruins of the original 14th century Château.

In 2015 we began an adventure to own a French Chateau. It has been a long journey, and in September of 2021 we became the protectors of this incredible property that we now call home. I keep an ongoing record of the long road to Château ownership, and you can visit our website by clicking on this link... https://www.atthechateau.com - If you would like to receive my newsletter that announces new posts, please visit the website and subscribe.

You can also find us on instagram at atthechateau.france or https://www.instagram.com/atthechateau.france/

And FaceBook at https://www.facebook.com/atthechateau.france

We would like to thank all of our Patrons who are helping to restore this historic monument, their contributions are invaluable to our efforts. If you would like to become a patron of Château Avensac, follow this link, https://www.patreon.com/chateauavensac

Please visit Chateau Arton Wines at, https://arton.fr

snippet.title: The Village of Avensac, home to our restoration project, Château Avensac
snippet.description:
Welcome to Château Avensac. Today are taking a walk through the Village of Avensac. Avensac is located in the Gers in the south France, between Bordeaux and Toulouse, and is home to our Chateau, which was built to protect the commune. From the village church to the Chateau, join Phillip on a short walk about town.

We are at the very beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us for this fascinating journey.

snippet.title: The Ancient Wing and a VERY special Interview ! at Château Avensac
snippet.description:
Welcome to Château Avensac. Today Phillip is going to show you around the Ancient wing of the Chateau built in 1320 and remodeled in the early 1800's. We also have in store for you a VERY special interview with an important member of our team who has refused to be seen on camera until now. We hope you enjoy todays journey as we further explore Chateau Avensac in the south of France.

We are at the very beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us for this fascinating journey.

snippet.title: What is happening in the Bedrooms of Château Avensac - PART ONE
snippet.description:
Welcome to Château Avensac. What are the bedrooms of the Chateau like? How many are there? What will become of poor Judy? Join us today as we discuss and have a look around some of the principle bedrooms of the Chateau, and of course we will address the Judy situation.

We are at the very beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us for this fascinating journey.

snippet.title: Evacuate the Château - Egyptian Style
snippet.description:
Welcome to Château Avensac ~ Join us today for an interesting and exciting look at Evacuating the Chateau, otherwise known as the creation of a new evacuation system, including a disturbing descent into a mysterious underground vault. All of your favorite characters are joining us today along with a couple of special guests. Please enjoy!

Be sure to visit our friends Vivienne and Simon, AKA Chateau Love https://www.youtube.com/@ChateauLove

We are at the very beginning of our Château restoration/renovation, and we hope you will like and subscribe to the channel and join us on this fascinating journey.

Des sous-titres français sont disponibles pour cette vidéo en cliquant sur le bouton sous-titres et en choisissant la langue française... profitez-en !

About us
Two American boys from California following a dream to purchase and restore a Historic Monument in the south of France. 

Our Channel, At the Chateau, focuses on the restoration and celebration of Château Avensac, a listed French castle, designed in the late 18th century, and built in the beginning of the 19th century, on the ruins of the original 14th century Château.

In 2015 we began an adventure to own a French Chateau. It has been a long journey, and in September of 2021 we became the guardians of this incredible property that we now call home. I keep an ongoing record of the long road to Château ownership, as well as our continued restoration work on our website. You can visit our website by clicking on the following link... https://www.atthechateau.com -
If you would like to receive my newsletter that announces new posts, please visit the website and subscribe.

snippet.title: IT'S FINALLY HAPPENING! Paint & Wallpaper REVEAL in the CHATEAU! - Journey to the Château, Ep. 219
snippet.description:
In this Friday episode, Patrick and Stuart are back in their chateau petit salon to start putting up the final paint and wallpaper from Little Greene Paint and Paper. This period reproduction wallpaper is an interpretation of one of Architect Robert Adam’s designs, and comes with exact match coordinating colors. John the Electrician stops by to update some of the salon electrics. Patrick and Stuart also meet up with friends Tony and Jane to go to a "Salon de Curiosités" antique fair at the beautiful Château d'Ainay-le-Vieil.

--------------
Music: 

Serenade, Op. 6, by Josef Suk
Performed by A Far Cry
From YouTube Audio Library

Parisian Café, by Aaron Kenny
From YouTube Audio Library

----------

Join Patrick and Stuart on their journey to find a neglected, forgotten, or crumbling château or castle in France, and then continue to follow them as they work on its restoration, rénovation, decoration, and furnishing.  Along the way, they will also create and share videos on their preparation for having gîtes for guests, and an event venue in their chateau (wedding, birthday, anniversary, organization or club meetings, retreats, etc.).

👍👍👍
If you like our videos, please hit the like button on the video, subscribe to our channel, and use the "share" feature below the video to share it with a friend. It will really help us out. Thank you! 🙏❤️

snippet.title: Château de Colombe and Le Tour de France! - Journey to the Château, Ep. 218
snippet.description:
In this Wednesday episode, Patrick and Stuart welcome friends and guests to the chateau for a party to celebrate the viewing of the Tour de France. Stage 10 of the 2024 Tour de France passes just 400 m from the front door of the Château de Colombe! They show highlights from the long caravan that precedes the peloton of cyclists, as well as the moment when the group of cyclists actually pass by. Patrick and Stuart also show the beginning of the renovation work in the chateau side kitchen with help from friend Tony @notquiteachateaudiy . 

--------------
Music: 

Dreams of a Child, by David Fesliyan
From Fesliyan Studios

Go Beyond, by David Fesliyan
From Fesliyan Studios

String Quartet in B-flat Major, (Erdody, Sunrise) Hob. III: 78 Op. 76 No. 4: Movement 3. Minuet. Allegro - Trio, by Joseph Haydn

snippet.title: Summer wonders and weather effects
snippet.description:
My mid-July tour shows strong new growth, after a cold and wet spring. Plants are wonderful and impress me so much, because we have had no significant warmth or sunshine..
Course dates coming up https://bookwhen.com/charlesdowding#focus=ev-silv-20240721103000
Discover how no dig soil quality helps plants through adverse conditions. And makes succession planting quick and easy.
Squash plants in the thumbnail have doubled size in two weeks, to 1.8m high in places.

Homeacres in Somerset UK is classed zone 8: like Texas! However since 1st June the average high temperature is just 19.4°C 69°F and the average low temperature is 9°C 48°F. The low night temperatures in particular have slowed the growth of many plants, especially cucurbits, capsicums and tomatoes.

My Crocus page has products such as wire hoops and mesh covers made of plant matter https://www.charlesdowding.co.uk/product/insectonet-plastic-free-insect-netting

Filmed by Nicola Smith on 11th July at Homeacres, Somerset UK.

15:17 Hedging, a midsummer job

snippet.title: Seeds YOU MUST Sow In July! | 10 Super Fast Growing Crops |Gardening For Beginners
snippet.description:
It may be the middle of summer and too late to sow many crops, such as tomatoes peppers and aubergines, just to name a few.. but there's still time to get some fast growing crops sown for some quick harvests before the end of the growing season.

I'm down on the allotment today going over some of the veggies you can sow in July. Some of these are great for successional sowings.
I'll be sowing some of these in my garden too! 
We're also thinking ahead to next year as well, so we will be planting some things so we can get an early crop next year!

I hope this video helps you guys out in some way.

If it did, press the like button and show your support. It means a lot. If you haven't already subscribed, and want to learn and grow with me, then you may want to consider subscribing to my channel and clicking the 'bell' icon too, and you'll never miss any new videos! 

Cheers!

localized.title: Seeds YOU MUST Sow In July! | 10 Super Fast Growing Crops |Gardening For Beginners
localized.description:
It may be the middle of summer and too late to sow many crops, such as tomatoes peppers and aubergines, just to name a few.. but there's still time to get some fast growing crops sown for some quick harvests before the end of the growing season.

I'm down on the allotment today going over some of the veggies you can sow in July. Some of these are great for successional sowings.
I'll be sowing some of these in my garden too! 
We're also thinking ahead to next year as well, so we will be planting some things so we can get an early crop next year!

I hope this video helps you guys out in some way.

If it did, press the like button and show your support. It means a lot. If you haven't already subscribed, and want to learn and grow with me, then you may want to consider subscribing to my channel and clicking the 'bell' icon too, and you'll never miss any new videos!

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Weird Things I Do in the Garden That Actually Work
snippet.description:
I learned how to garden on the go while raising four young children. I didn't even know enough to know all the "rules" I was breaking. I was just having fun and figuring things out as I went. And it turns out, I still like my way of doing things, even though most people find it weird. 

Here are some "weird" things you can start trying out in your garden to make it more fun and maybe even work better than the "right way" to do things.

snippet.title: 5 Things You Can Eat from the Garden Every Day Even If You're Not a Homesteader
snippet.description:
I am many things, but a homesteader is not one of them. What I am is BUSY. If you're busy, too, you can still grow food to enjoy daily with less than half an hour of tending each week. snippet.title: 3 Reasons to Stop Gardening with Fertilizer (and What to Do Instead)
snippet.description:
You don't have to douse your plants in Miracle-Gro to grow an abundant and beautiful garden. You don't even have to use fertilizer at all. (I don't!)

Now, I'm not talking about natural minerals or animal products. I'm talking about synthetic materials. Here's why I think you should stop using fertilizer in your garden and what to do to nourish your veggies instead. 

Shop Kitchen Garden Revival if you still need to set your garden up: https://shop.gardenary.com/collections/books/products/kitchen-garden-revival

snippet.title: Rewild your garden - but it's not just about letting everything go!
snippet.description:
If you want to encourage wildlife or you're gardening in difficult conditions, then rewilding - or picking up some elements of rewilding could work well for you. Here environmental activist and film-maker Serena Schellenberg shows us round her rewilded garden and explains how it's an easy way of gardening, even for beginners.
00:00 Is rewilding gardening at all?
00:12 The Rewilded Garden, RHS Chelsea Flower Show 2022: https://www.rewildingbritain.org.uk/about-us/how-we-work/rhs-chelsea-flower-show
00:46 Rewilding is not just about letting everything go
00:50 The Book Of Wilding by Isabella Tree and Charlie Burrell https://amzn.to/3S64hD3 (Links to Amazon are affiliate, see below).
01:46 The difference between a nature friendly garden and a rewilded garden
02:35 Flooding means that a traditional garden wouldn't work
03:12 Main steps in rewilding
04:14 Why rewilding is an easy way of maintaining a garden
05:13 Knepp Estate: https://knepp.co.uk/knepp-estate/gardens/rewild-a-garden/
05:51 What has worked best in Serena's garden
07:04 Weeding in a rewilded garden
07:55 The grass is cut down in autumn (fall)
08:18 Invasive plants
10:00 Seating areas and ornaments provide focal points and definition
11:30 How to create a stumpery in a large or small garden: https://youtu.be/vqQMq_RuiAs

For garden ideas, gardening advice, garden design and landscaping ideas for your garden or backyard, subscribe to the Middlesized Garden YouTube channel here: https://www.youtube.com/c/ThemiddlesizedgardenCoUk

Whether you love English garden style, cottage gardens or contemporary urban gardening, The Middlesized Garden has gardening advice and garden ideas for you.

Weekly videos cover gardening advice and garden design  - from small space gardens to middle-sized garden landscaping - plus garden tours and tips for container gardening. 

The Middlesized Garden practices sustainability, wildlife gardening and no till methods. If your garden backyard is smaller than an acre, join us and enjoy your garden even more!
The Middlesized Garden Complete Guide to Garden Privacy is available in Kindle or paperback in 13 countries (in English only). If you'd like your garden to feel more private, click here for availability in your country: https://www.themiddlesizedgarden.co.uk/books/the-complete-guide-to-garden-privacy/

snippet.title: Is floral design easy? Design a flower arrangement using a flower frog a simple design tool #flowers
snippet.description: Join me in this flower arrangement tutorial where I show you how to create a beautiful modern garden style arrangement using a flower frog. You might be wondering, is floral design easy? Well, with my step-by-step instructions, you'll be amazed at how simple it is to create a stunning floral arrangement. We start with bellflowers to create the structure, then use a garden rose as the focal point, add some spray roses to fill out the shape, and ranunculus to create movement. To fill in the holes, we add more roses with a beautiful scent and finish off with star of Bethlehem that will continue blooming day after day. Follow along and learn how to create your own gorgeous flower arrangement today! #flowerarrangement #flowertutorial #easycenterpiece #floralstyling #diyflower #floraldesign

snippet.title: How to use Flower Frogs to Display Cut Flowers
snippet.description:
Have you ever wanted to quickly and simply display a few flowers without using floral foam or a conventional vase? The solution is a flower frog, otherwise known as a kenzan. In this video, I demonstrate how easy flower frogs are to use without any flower-arranging experience.

Flower frogs are reusable, durable, weighted holders for cut flowers. They can transform the smallest egg cup or largest dish into a vessel fit for a top florist. Originally used for Ikebana, the ancient Japanese art of flower arranging, the ease with which they make cut flowers and foliage come alive in a modern, contemporary way is now appreciated worldwide.

You can shop from a wide range of flower frogs, decorative bowls and flower scissors on my website at www.dancoopergarden.com.

00:00 Introduction.
00:09 What is a flower frog?
00:44 Different shapes and sizes of flower frogs.
01:22 Using flower-shaped bowls.
01:42 Getting started with your arrangement.
02:28 Placing the stems on your flower frog.
04:54 Take a step back to check your display.
05:10 What do with very short stems.
05:25 How to disguise the flower frog.
06:20 Where to buy.

snippet.title: How to use a flower frog! | Episode 28 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Pin frogs have been used as a floral mechanic for years and date back to 14th century Japan (called a Kenzan in that culture)!   They were popularized in the US during the 40’s and 50’s.  The “frog” is a device used to help hold flowers in place.  They are made of different materials and are typically very eco-friendly because they can be cleaned and re-used!  See how easy they are to use in creating striking floral arrangements!  Then, the pour for this episode was gifted to me by a great friend!  It’s called New Southern Revival Sorghum Whiskey from the High Wire Distilling Company in Charleston, SC.  The spirit is completely made from 100% sorghum syrup and while you would expect it to be quite sweet, it’s not overly so!  The husband and wife owners have a background in backing so their approach is very much culinary-focused!  I hope you’ll enjoy this episode! 

Come say Hi!
https://www.facebook.com/Creative-Occasions-Events-Flowers-Gifts-278597787693
https://www.instagram.com/creativeoccasionsevents

snippet.title: Color Theory 101 for your Flower Arrangements | Episode 35 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Whatever the theme or occasion, the color scheme is often one of the first considerations of creating a floral design.  In this episode, we take a look at the color wheel and talk about 3 basic color ways and what makes up each!  We discuss shades and tones and have floral examples of each!  For the bourbon portion of this episode, I’ll be sampling a new-to-me product called Baby Blue Corn Whiskey!  It hails from the Balcones Distillery in Waco, Texas and is described as an “intentionally youthful” pour!  With notes of melted butter and vanilla, you may want to try this one too!  Hope you enjoy this episode!

snippet.title: Using the Principle of Rhythm in Floral Design | Episode 24 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Rhythm is an important aspect of floral design, allowing the viewers eye to move across and around the design.  In this video, I’ll show you how you can create rhythm by repeating elements in the design as well as the products themselves creating a sense of movement!  This is a fun one for sure!  Bardstown Fusion # 7 from Bardstown, Kentucky is the featured bourbon!  It’s created through the blending of old (12-year) and new (3-year) products, designed to create a totally unique spirit experience.  I hope you’ll enjoy this episode!

snippet.title: How to use the Banding Technique in Floral Design | Episode 10 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
In this episode, learn how to use banding as a decorative technique in floral design to hold groups of flowers together.   We use a vibrant and fun color palette to showcase this contemporary style.  A clear glass container shows off this decorative technique to its full potential.  We’ll even use a tall martini glass for an example of banding as it might be used in an event design.  We’ll also be tasting Elijah Craig Small Batch bourbon.  This is a delicious 94 proof pour with notes of smoky oak and vanilla!

snippet.title: Leaf Manipulation in Floral Design | Episode 40 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Leaf manipulation is a design technique that will elevate your floral arrangements to the next level!  Watch as I show you five different ways to change up the look of aspidistra foliage.  And, maybe even create and all foliage arrangement!  Then, we’ll continue our visit to Brady’s Distillery right here in Roanoke, Virginia for a tasting not often experienced!  Five year 120 proof Brady’s bourbon straight from the barrel!  Join me for a fun episode all around.  Cheers, friend!

snippet.title: Contemporary Event Floral Design | Episode 56 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Learn the trick of this unusual mechanic to create a contemporary floral design on the outside of the container!  Duct tape, dry floral foam and pan glue work to create the mechanic of the design adhered to a large glass vase.  Add water and floating candles for an elegant party design. The pour for this episode is a gifted bottle from my friend Dean (I have the BEST friends!).  Picked up on his way back from New Orleans, this J.T. Meleck whiskey has a 100% rice mashbill!  Aged in American oak barrels, I think you’ll find this whiskey a very pleasant surprise!  Hope you enjoy this episode.  Cheers y’all!

snippet.title: Iris and Tulip Ikebana design | Episode 55 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
Watch how the classic pin frog brings this ikebana design to life.  We make use of two stars of the spring flower world – iris and tulips in a vibrant complimentary color scheme of purple and orange.  Add in some dried branches for extra movement and height and we’re all done with this simple but dramatic design. And, while I design, I’ll be sipping on E.H. Taylor, from the Buffalo Trace distillery in Frankfurt, KY.  This highly sought-after pour is easy and smooth – perfect for a spring evening around your fire pit!  Hope you enjoy this episode.  Cheers y’all!

snippet.title: Facebook Poll Winners come to life! | Episode 52 of Blossoms and Bourbon
snippet.description:
The results of the poll are in and now let’s see what happens!  The poll ran both on Instagram and Facebook, so we will have an episode dedicated to each!  This is the Facebook design and, I love it just as much as the IG one!  A bold and contemporary choice, the vase, the mechanic and the color scheme are AMAZING. For our pour, we sample the highly sought after Wellers Special Reserve!  Touted as the original wheated bourbon, it is an easy sipper that will appeal to many palettes!  Hope you enjoy this episode and pour! Cheers, my friends!

snippet.title: 永久保存版｜很實用的3個插花技術
snippet.description:
插花基本教學，新手必看!  插花教程 插花入門 日式插花教學

【線上花藝課程】申請 https://forms.gle/FfboGzU1KzTnxSnv7 
花道家 宫本理城 1976年出生于东京。 从两岁起跟随作为古流东洋会的创始人同时也是我的祖母服部理春和二代家元宮本理峰我的母亲学习插花。大学时起参加插花展览会。参加过世界花道大会和日本花道艺术展。2009年被任命为古流东洋会本家副手。 之后，应邀参加了突尼斯共和国，沙特阿拉伯举办的“Jenadriyah活动节”和莫斯科柴可夫斯基纪念国立音乐学院主办的“日本之心”国际节，并在俄罗斯莫斯科进行了插花表演。获得全日本花道大赛评审团特别奖。花道艺术协会的正式会员。花道国际会员。
 https://www.rijo.jp/

snippet.title: 胖周瑜心腹傳訊成羈押鐵證？ 應訊前先串證？ 網驚：朝中真的有人？《庶民大頭家》完整版 20240712 #鄭麗文 #謝寒冰 #林郁方 #帥化民 @chinatvnews
snippet.description:
鄭文燦涉貪該不該收押，在法院拉鋸多日，昨天法院裁定鄭文燦羈押禁見，前兩次鄭文燦都成功交保，這次失利的關鍵就在於檢方在法院指出，鄭文燦在7/5應訊前，以Line告知施姓秘書的訊息，內容竟與被告應訊時答辯方向相同，顯見鄭文燦應訊前，就有管道獲知檢察官偵辦內容，並擬妥答辯方向，而施姓祕書更多次居間與涉案地主傳遞訊息，顯見有串證之虞，現在也曝光鄭文燦的心腹秘書施彥廷，過去是太陽花的決策要角，在鄭文燦擔任機要.副主任，在鄭文燦身邊長達10年，過去施彥廷分享要當鄭文燦秘書，就是要主動積極.有執行力，鄭文燦收賄按壓了7年才辦，在7/5檢方約談前，鄭文燦就知曉是什麼案子，還很有行動力的預做準備，這不就表示蔡英文既使交棒下台，朝中仍然有人讓大阿哥撐腰?

snippet.title: Will Biden Go? Roundtable Discussion with David Dayen, Medea Benjamin & Bill Fletcher Jr.
snippet.description:
Support our work: https://democracynow.org/donate/sm-desc-yt

As the world watched Thursday night, President Biden held his first solo press conference this year, after hosting a NATO conference in which he accidentally referred to Ukrainian President Zelensky as Russian President Putin before quickly correcting himself. While speaking with reporters, Biden defended his record and vowed to “finish the job,” but at one point referred to Kamala Harris as “Vice President Trump.” As more Democrats continue to call for him to step aside, we host a roundtable discussion on Biden and Trump and the 2024 race, and the impact on U.S. foreign policy, with American Prospect executive editor David Dayen; longtime labor, racial justice and international activist Bill Fletcher Jr., co-founder of the Ukrainian Solidarity Network; and CodePink co-founder Medea Benjamin, co-author of the books NATO: What You Need to Know and War in Ukraine: Making Sense of a Senseless Conflict.

Democracy Now! is an independent global news hour that airs on over 1,500 TV and radio stations Monday through Friday. Watch our livestream at democracynow.org Mondays to Fridays 8-9 a.m. ET.

snippet.title: 'Joe Biden got testy': US President 'snaps' at reporters in Italy
snippet.description:
US President Joe Biden recently got "testy" before "snapping" at reporters who were simply doing their job, says Sky News Australia host James Morrow. 

Mr Morrow assessed footage of Joe Biden  answering questions at a media conference after G7 meetings in Italy. 

"It didn't take long for Biden to get testy – snapping at American reporters for doing their job rather than sticking to the White House's tightly controlled script," Mr Morrow said.

snippet.title: Sky News host bursts out laughing at 'dimwitted lefties' from The View
snippet.description:
Sky News host Rita Panahi couldn’t contain her laughter over “dimwitted lefties” on The View discussing the influx of illegal migrants in New York City. 

“But what is the Biden administration, which has overseen record numbers crossing that southern border illegally, millions every year, what are they going to do?” Ms Panahi said. 

“Well, this is their latest genius idea, no they’re not going to complete the wall, they’re not going to implement tough border protection policies, they’re going to try to keep the illegal migrants in Texas.” 

The LA Times reported the Biden administration was considering a plan to force illegal immigrants to remain in Texas while awaiting asylum screenings. 

“Genius, genius – why should Texans have to deal with this crisis, they aren’t the ones voting for sanctuary city mayors and governors,” Ms Panahi said.

snippet.title: Lefties losing it: Sky News host roasts 'leftie' Jill Biden after Trump rant
snippet.description:
The hosts of American talk show 'The View' are keen to show "misery loves company" with US First Lady Jill Biden being the latest "leftie" to lose it on the program, says Sky News Australia host Rita Panahi. 

"You'd think there was enough weapon-grade crazy on The View from the miserable wackadoodle hosts – but no, the ladies of The View are keen to prove that misery loves company," Ms Panahi said. 

"And they invite other lefties to lose it on their program, including the First Lady." 

While talking on the panel, Jill Biden and others took aim at former US president Donald Trump.

Ms Biden said Donald Trump "can't put a sentence together".

"You'd think there was enough weapon-grade crazy on The View from the miserable wackadoodle hosts – but no, the ladies of The View are keen to prove that misery loves company," Ms Panahi said. 

"And they invite other lefties to lose it on their program, including the First Lady." 

While talking on the panel, Jill Biden and others took aim at former US president Donald Trump.

Ms Biden said Donald Trump "can't put a sentence together".

snippet.title: Lefties losing it: Rita Panahi roasts 'bitter, broken' View hosts
snippet.description:
Sky News Australia host Rita Panahi says the hosts of American talk show 'The View' are so "bitter, broken, and miserable". 

Ms Panahi says each and every episode of The View showcases “just how broken the hosts are”.

“You know we can never go too long in this segment without featuring the work of the ladies of The View,” Ms Panahi said.

“Each and every episode showcases just how broken the hosts are, including the alpha female of the pack, Whoopi, who cannot even bring herself to say Trump’s name without spitting – gross.

“They are so bitter, broken and miserable – not sure why that makes me smile, but it does.”

snippet.title: Was There An Advanced Civilization Before Humans? | Answers With Joe
snippet.description:
Get 20% off your first order when you use the promo code "joescott" at http://www.mackweldon.com.
It took humans 10,000 years to go from hunter-gatherers to world domination. Considering the vastness of time that humans and life have been on Earth, could this have happened once before?

This question was put forth by Adam Frank and Gavin Schmidt in their paper titled The Silurian Hypothesis, where they tried to figure out what in the geologic record would be a sign of a previous industrial civilization. It brings up a lot of questions and makes you deal with the weight of deep time, as well as the fleeting nature of history.

Watch this video ad-free on Nebula: https://nebula.tv/videos/joe-scott-was-there-an-advanced-civilization-before-humans

snippet.title: Could You REALLY Survive A Trip To Mars? | Answers With Joe
snippet.description:
Get 30 days of CuriosityStream for free, just go to http://www.curiositystream.com/joescott
We've been talking about going to Mars since the end of the Apollo program. Now there's a new wave of interest in traveling to the Red Planet - but the challenges that wait for those who take the trip are bigger than most think - and possibly unsurmountable.


Support me on Patreon!
http://www.patreon.com/answerswithjoe

Get cool nerdy t-shirts at
http://www.answerswithjoe.com/shirts

Interested in getting a Tesla? Use my referral link and get discounts and perks:
https://ts.la/joe74700

Become a channel member and get access to exclusive livestreams and content here:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-2YHgc363EdcusLIBbgxzg/join

Follow me at all my places!
Instagram: https://instagram.com/answerswithjoe
Snapchat: https://www.snapchat.com/add/answerswithjoe
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/answerswithjoe
Twitter: https://www.twitter.com/answerswithjoe

The human body is adapted for living here on Earth and nowhere else in the universe. Just a few of the problems we'll find going to Mars are:

The effects of weightlessness. Astronauts who have been on long-duration flights to the ISS have experienced vision problems, cardiovascular issues, bone loss, elevated CO2 levels, reduced cognition, and more.

All of these issues will be exacerbated on a Mars trip because the shortest trip to Mars would be far longer than the longest any human has ever been in space (Valeri Polyakov spent 14 months in space in 1995).

Radiation and cosmic rays will be an issue. Almost all of the time we've spent in space has been in low Earth orbit (LEO), which is under the Earth's magnetic shield. The trip to Mars would expose the passengers to all the solar radiation and comic rays that our magnetic shield blocks, and studies have shown that the 24 Apollo astronauts that flew to the Moon showed a 5x greater incidence of cardiovascular disease later in life.

Immune system issues. Studies have shown that astronauts' immune systems are reduced when weightless and bacteria become stronger at the same time. Outbreaks in the enclosed environment on Mars would be an issue.

The conditions of Mars. Mars only has 1% of the atmosphere of Earth and even that is carbon dioxide, which we can't breathe. It also makes temperatures vary widely. Plus the soil is filled with perchlorate, which affects our endocrine system and can cause breathing problems.

Perchlorate:
https://www.epa.gov/sites/production/files/2014-03/documents/ffrrofactsheet_contaminant_perchlorate_january2014_final.pdf

snippet.title: Are We Really Alone In The Universe? | Answers With Joe
snippet.description:
Get Curiositystream for free for 30 days if you go to http://www.curiositystream.com/joescott

The Rare Earth Hypothesis is the idea that the conditions that created life on Earth are so specific to this planet that it can't happen anywhere else in the universe. Here's some of the evidence to back this up.


Support me on Patreon!
http://www.patreon.com/answerswithjoe

Get cool nerdy t-shirts at
http://www.answerswithjoe.com/shirts

Become a channel member and get access to exclusive livestreams and content here:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-2YHgc363EdcusLIBbgxzg/join

Follow me at all my places!
Instagram: https://instagram.com/answerswithjoe
Snapchat: https://www.snapchat.com/add/answerswithjoe
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/answerswithjoe
Twitter: https://www.twitter.com/answerswithjoe

====================

The Rare Earth Hypothesis something of a solution to the Fermi Paradox that points to several characteristics of Earth that may be required to keep life stable long enough to become intelligent, and these several traits may be incredibly unique in the universe, making intelligent life in the universe incredibly rare.

Some of these factors include:

Special place in the Milky Way
It turns out our position in the Milky way might be beneficial as the low star density prevents other stars from messing up our orbits.

The right type of star.
Our sun is a G2 main sequence star that remains stable for a very long time.

Rocky planet in the Goldilocks zone
Earth is just the right distance from the sun to form liquid water.

Magnetic Shield
We're the only rocky planet with a magnetic shield protecting us from solar radiation.

Jupiter
Jupiter and the outer gas giants protect us from asteroid and comet impacts, and this might be rare in the universe.

Tectonic activity
We're the only planet with tectonic plates constantly rebuilding the crust.

snippet.description:

We live on a water planet. And the currents generated in the oceans affect all of our lives, even if you don't live near the ocean. snippet.title: Venus Used To Be A Lot More Like Earth | Answers With Joe
snippet.description:
Use code JOESCOTT14 for up to 14 FREE MEALS + 3 Free Gifts across 5 HelloFresh boxes plus free shipping at https://bit.ly/3pkycbs
Venus has long been called Earth's twin, because our sizes are so similar. But as we learned in the early 60s, on our surface we couldn't be more different. This wasn't always the case though. It's thought that up until about 500 million years ago, our planets were very similar, in fact Venus may have supported life. So what happened?

snippet.title: Space Shades: Humanity's Last Hope | Answers With Joe
snippet.description:
The first 1000 people to sign up at https://skl.sh/joescott15 will get 2 free months of Skillshare Premium for free!
Space shades are often touted as our last hope if our climate change situation gets too out of control. If we can't keep carbon emissions down, we could just block the sun. I hear this option get thrown out very casually, but I've never seen a realistic look at what that would look like. How big would it need to be? How much would it cost? Wound it even work? So I decided to take a serious deep dive.

Here's the link to the paper by professor Roger Angel:
https://www.pnas.org/content/103/46/17184

Animations and shade designs by Kimi Talvitie: Find more of his work on Twitter: @kimitalvitie

Ethan Siegel's take on Starts With A Bang:
https://medium.com/starts-with-a-bang/ask-ethan-can-we-build-a-sun-screen-to-combat-global-climate-change-c6399f279ef
